    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-01T14:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-01T14:40:00-05:00" n="239"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1215.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-01T15:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 1, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Answering several matters in your January 30, 7 p.m. Five thousand dollars per
                    diem will keep Government alive if Vick can provide same. No danger of
                    revolutionists being paid but we must watch bad paper held by military
                    blackmailers of Arias stripe. The commercial attaché with power of comptroller
                    is ample safeguard, however. Can have powers of commercial attaché well defined
                    in letter of request for his appointment. I have on foot already a letter which
                    gives him “control of” daily expenditures. See despatch No. 46 and cable January
                    22, noon. On foot also a [letter] requesting that such a commercial attaché be
                    named. Will have letter written by Dominican Government as you instruct but I
                    venture to ask if language of January 26, 3 p.m. instruction concerning
                    commercial attaché duties, is sufficiently certain and definite? If Department
                    desires any change please wire text of clause to be inserted in said letter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
